HEADWORD: felid
<hw>felid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of various lithe-bodied
round-headed fissiped mammals, many with retractile claws; a member of
the <fam>Felidae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> feline.</syn>⟦br⟧
